<MarketingLayout
  title="Commitment to Open Source"
  description="How Silitics keeps the Rugix project open and independent."
>
  <h1>Commitment to Open Source</h1>

  <p>
    Rugix is developed by <a href="https://silitics.com">Silitics</a>, a
    company 100% owned and led by its founder
    <a href="https://github.com/koehlma">Maximilian Köhl</a>. The various
    tools of the Rugix Project have been developed out of the concrete needs
    and requirements of our clients' projects and the strong belief that we
    can do better when it comes to building reliable embedded devices.
  </p>
  <p>
    We fund the development of Rugix through consulting and system
    development work for clients, as well as through
    <a href="https://nexigon.cloud">Nexigon</a>, our commercial fleet
    management platform. We aim for a <strong>clean separation between the
    open-source project and our commercial offerings</strong>. Mixing the
    two creates conflicts of interest that would ultimately hurt both. We
    want Rugix to grow independently, on its own merit. As an example,
    <a href="/blog/efficient-delta-updates">delta updates</a> are a feature
    we built into Rugix, even though other "open core" vendors reserve them
    for their paid tiers.
  </p>
  <p>
    To that end, <strong>we are committed to keeping this project open-source
    and permissively licensed</strong> for the benefit of everyone.
    Concretely, this means:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      Rugix tools will remain open-source under their current permissive
      licenses (MIT and Apache 2.0).
    </li>
    <li>
      We will not degrade Rugix functionality to push people toward Nexigon
      or other offerings.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>We will not reject any contributions to existing Rugix tools
      solely on the grounds that they are in conflict with current commercial
      offerings.</strong> This includes integrations with fleet management
      solutions that compete with Nexigon.
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    We strive for maximal transparency with users, contributors, and
    supporters. If you have any questions or concerns, please reach out to
    us.
  </p>
</MarketingLayout>
